HEADWORD: Tartrovinic
<hw>Tar`tro*vin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tartro-</ets> + <ets>vinic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a certain acid composed of
tartaric acid in combination with ethyl, and now called
<xex>ethyltartaric acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
